# Database Schema

## Engine selection

Database engine is controlled by Spring profile in `application.properties`:

```
spring.profiles.active=hsqldb,spring-data-jpa
```

Three engines: `hsqldb` (default, in-memory), `mysql`, `postgresql`. Each has its own properties file and DDL scripts under `src/main/resources/db/<engine>/`.

## Schema conventions

- All tables use `INTEGER IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY` for IDs (except `users` which uses `username VARCHAR(20)` as PK)
- Foreign keys are explicit `ALTER TABLE ... ADD CONSTRAINT` statements
- Indexes exist on frequently queried columns (`owners.last_name`, `pets.name`, etc.)
- `initDB.sql` drops all tables in reverse FK order, then creates them
- `populateDB.sql` inserts seed data — all three engines share the same logical seed data

## When modifying schema

- Update `initDB.sql` and `populateDB.sql` for ALL THREE engines (`hsqldb/`, `mysql/`, `postgresql/`)
- Keep the logical schema identical across engines; only syntax should differ
- There is no Flyway/Liquibase — schema changes are raw DDL
- Set `ddl-auto=none` — Hibernate does not manage the schema
